359
00:21:27,240 --> 00:21:28,480
Can I help you?

360
00:21:30,656 --> 00:21:32,519
Where is
the juvenile prosecution office?

361
00:21:32,519 --> 00:21:33,359
It's here.

362
00:21:43,284 --> 00:21:44,416
(Logistics)

363
00:21:46,319 --> 00:21:47,880
Doesn't it say Logistics?

364
00:21:51,219 --> 00:21:53,408
(Juvenile Prosecution Office)

365
00:21:58,759 --> 00:21:59,519
Show him around.

366
00:21:59,519 --> 00:22:00,279
I have a meeting.

367
00:22:01,640 --> 00:22:02,960
When will you be back?

368
00:22:10,519 --> 00:22:12,480
(Juvenile Prosecution Office)
Well, Captain Bai.

369
00:22:12,799 --> 00:22:14,016
Why don't you take a seat?

370
00:22:23,559 --> 00:22:25,759
Is this really
the juvenile prosecution office?

371
00:22:26,359 --> 00:22:27,160
Yeah.

372
00:22:29,960 --> 00:22:31,160
Liu, here for the rice?

373
00:22:33,839 --> 00:22:35,039
Give me a hand, buddy.

374
00:22:40,359 --> 00:22:41,160
This...

375
00:22:41,160 --> 00:22:42,079
This...

376
00:22:42,079 --> 00:22:43,039
This...

377
00:22:43,640 --> 00:22:45,240
This is the juvenile prosecution office?

378
00:22:45,759 --> 00:22:47,240
Whose office looks like this?

379
00:22:47,440 --> 00:22:48,720
Calm down.

380
00:22:48,720 --> 00:22:49,640
That was my reaction

381
00:22:49,640 --> 00:22:51,079
when I first came here.

382
00:22:51,559 --> 00:22:53,079
This is temporary.

383
00:22:53,359 --> 00:22:55,960
Our new office is under renovation.

384
00:22:56,319 --> 00:22:57,279
It's luxurious.

385
00:22:57,480 --> 00:22:59,200
You could say it's lavish.

386
00:22:59,319 --> 00:23:02,000
It is an important department. Isn't it?

387
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:03,160
Yes, it is.

388
00:23:03,559 --> 00:23:04,839
Important pilot department.

389
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:06,359
Why a pilot department?

390
00:23:07,279 --> 00:23:09,119
Because it will be important.

391
00:23:10,200 --> 00:23:11,599
With just three people?

392
00:23:12,079 --> 00:23:13,519
No, two people.

393
00:23:13,519 --> 00:23:14,640
Zhitao and you.

394
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:16,960
I'm just a clerk

395
00:23:16,960 --> 00:23:18,839
who assists you guys.

396
00:23:19,559 --> 00:23:21,200
I must talk to Prosecutor Zheng.

397
00:23:21,799 --> 00:23:23,160
This is way too far-fetched.

398
00:23:23,640 --> 00:23:24,640
She's not here.

399
00:23:25,160 --> 00:23:26,160
She's out of town.

400
00:23:27,119 --> 00:23:28,440
Besides, why would you

401
00:23:28,440 --> 00:23:29,640
speak to her now?

402
00:23:30,279 --> 00:23:31,960
She picked you out of thousands.

403
00:23:32,359 --> 00:23:33,559
Are you going to

404
00:23:33,559 --> 00:23:35,319
question her judgment?

405
00:23:36,799 --> 00:23:38,039
It's highly inappropriate.

406
00:23:45,279 --> 00:23:46,200
Besides,

407
00:23:46,440 --> 00:23:47,839
there are good aspects

408
00:23:48,079 --> 00:23:49,559
about our office.

409
00:23:49,920 --> 00:23:50,200
Right?

410
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:50,599
Cheng.

411
00:23:51,160 --> 00:23:51,839
Ms. Li.

412
00:23:57,599 --> 00:23:58,559
You've worked hard.

413
00:23:59,039 --> 00:24:00,039
Handsome young man.

414
00:24:00,799 --> 00:24:01,279
Yeah.

415
00:24:03,119 --> 00:24:03,599
You see?

416
00:24:04,240 --> 00:24:05,319
This is the good aspect?

417
00:24:05,559 --> 00:24:06,119
Tell me.

418
00:24:06,119 --> 00:24:07,400
Where is the good aspect?

419
00:24:07,400 --> 00:24:08,720
Why can't I see it?

420
00:24:08,720 --> 00:24:09,799
There are good aspects.

421
00:24:12,480 --> 00:24:13,319
Look.

422
00:24:13,799 --> 00:24:15,079
Printing is so easy

423
00:24:15,759 --> 00:24:16,599
here.

424
00:24:16,640 --> 00:24:18,279
Also, if you need pens or notebooks,

425
00:24:18,279 --> 00:24:19,920
you can get them right here.

426
00:24:20,759 --> 00:24:22,839
It's also very convenient
to use the water closet.

427
00:24:35,956 --> 00:24:38,368
(People's Procuratorate of Yunhai)

428
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:40,480
Files of the past two months.

429
00:24:40,839 --> 00:24:43,279
Zhitao said that she wanted you

430
00:24:43,279 --> 00:24:44,960
to read them as soon as possible.

431
00:24:45,799 --> 00:24:48,960
The case of the organized theft
has been concluded.

432
00:24:49,200 --> 00:24:52,200
There was an accessory in this case.

433
00:24:52,440 --> 00:24:55,000
That was Lu Guangfu,
Lu Sheng and Lu Ming's father.

434
00:24:55,599 --> 00:24:56,759
Lu Guangfu

435
00:24:57,079 --> 00:24:58,319
has admitted

436
00:24:58,640 --> 00:25:01,319
to renting his children
to the criminal gang.

437
00:25:01,319 --> 00:25:03,400
He's sentenced to one year in prison.

438
00:25:04,359 --> 00:25:05,599
He seriously violated

439
00:25:05,599 --> 00:25:08,359
the lawful rights
and interests of the ward.

440
00:25:08,519 --> 00:25:10,480
Even after he is released,

441
00:25:10,480 --> 00:25:11,839
his younger son Lu Ming

442
00:25:11,839 --> 00:25:13,359
will still be underage.

443
00:25:13,559 --> 00:25:14,799
It will be detrimental

444
00:25:14,799 --> 00:25:15,799
to the child

445
00:25:15,799 --> 00:25:17,920
if he continues to live with Lu Guangfu.

446
00:25:18,119 --> 00:25:20,599
Therefore, we plan to suggest

447
00:25:20,960 --> 00:25:22,839
the Civil Affairs Department
file a lawsuit

448
00:25:22,839 --> 00:25:24,480
to revoke Lu Guangfu's guardianship.

449
00:25:32,480 --> 00:25:34,720
This is very meaningful

450
00:25:34,759 --> 00:25:35,960
and quite pioneering.

451
00:25:37,160 --> 00:25:39,960
It's worth encouraging that Lin

452
00:25:40,279 --> 00:25:41,119
brought it up.

453
00:25:42,799 --> 00:25:44,559
What do you think?

454
00:25:46,880 --> 00:25:48,079
I'll go first.

455
00:25:49,319 --> 00:25:52,559
I am personally against this practice.

456
00:25:54,839 --> 00:25:55,759
The reason is simple.

457
00:25:56,640 --> 00:25:57,599
I can't find

458
00:25:57,839 --> 00:26:00,200
any legal basis for the procuratorate

459
00:26:00,200 --> 00:26:01,160
to take the lead.

460
00:26:03,160 --> 00:26:03,920
Prosecutor Lin,

461
00:26:04,359 --> 00:26:07,039
your proposal references
the General Rules of Civil Law.

462
00:26:08,240 --> 00:26:08,920
I suggest that

463
00:26:08,920 --> 00:26:10,759
the Civil Affairs Department
file a lawsuit

464
00:26:11,160 --> 00:26:13,240
and that the procuratorate support it.

465
00:26:13,880 --> 00:26:15,559
Article 18 of the Civil Law stipulates

466
00:26:15,960 --> 00:26:18,079
that the guardians who fail
to fulfill their duties

467
00:26:18,240 --> 00:26:20,839
or infringe upon the lawful rights
and interests of the ward

468
00:26:20,839 --> 00:26:22,039
shall bear legal liabilities.

469
00:26:22,480 --> 00:26:24,519
Upon the application
of relevant personnel or units,

470
00:26:24,519 --> 00:26:26,112
the People's Court can revoke

471
00:26:26,400 --> 00:26:27,880
the guardian's qualification.

472
00:26:29,960 --> 00:26:30,880
When was Article 18

473
00:26:30,880 --> 00:26:32,799
written into
the General Rules of Civil Law?

474
00:26:34,519 --> 00:26:35,480
In 1986.

475
00:26:37,119 --> 00:26:38,160
It's been 28 years.

476
00:26:39,039 --> 00:26:40,240
Has there ever been

477
00:26:40,240 --> 00:26:42,160
a precedent for revoking guardianship?

478
00:26:42,160 --> 00:26:42,759
No.

479
00:26:43,640 --> 00:26:44,720
The law has never

480
00:26:44,720 --> 00:26:46,279
been practiced since 1986.

481
00:26:46,440 --> 00:26:47,640
You want to use it now.

482
00:26:48,440 --> 00:26:52,160
Do you know the impact it may have
on the national judicial system?

483
00:26:52,160 --> 00:26:53,200
No, I don't.

484
00:26:53,559 --> 00:26:55,720
There is the law and the need.

485
00:26:56,119 --> 00:26:58,359
I don't know why we should
stick to judicial conventions

486
00:26:58,359 --> 00:27:00,400
and whether anyone has done this.

487
00:27:02,440 --> 00:27:05,480
Lu Guangfu's wife, Zhu Chongyan,

488
00:27:05,720 --> 00:27:06,640
has a mental illness

489
00:27:07,279 --> 00:27:09,839
and can't serve as a guardian.

490
00:27:10,400 --> 00:27:12,160
Who is going to take care

491
00:27:12,319 --> 00:27:13,400
of this child?

492
00:27:13,920 --> 00:27:16,160
The Civil Affairs Department.

493
00:27:17,559 --> 00:27:19,960
You're assigning them tasks?

494
00:27:20,440 --> 00:27:22,240
What if our proposal

495
00:27:22,359 --> 00:27:24,240
put the Civil Affairs Department

496
00:27:25,599 --> 00:27:27,160
in a difficult position?

497
00:27:33,440 --> 00:27:34,079
Animals!

498
00:27:34,240 --> 00:27:35,400
Outrageous.

499
00:27:37,559 --> 00:27:38,440
Not you.

500
00:27:38,640 --> 00:27:39,880
The bad guys.

501
00:28:01,119 --> 00:28:01,984
Where are you going?

502
00:28:02,720 --> 00:28:03,240
Home.

503
00:28:03,519 --> 00:28:04,279
Give me the report.

504
00:28:04,480 --> 00:28:05,279
What report?

505
00:28:05,880 --> 00:28:07,079
Those were novels?

506
00:28:10,960 --> 00:28:12,039
Can I write it tomorrow?

507
00:28:12,039 --> 00:28:13,240
Finish your job today.

508
00:28:13,359 --> 00:28:14,359
I'll write at home.

509
00:28:14,359 --> 00:28:15,960
No, there are confidentiality rules.

510
00:28:16,359 --> 00:28:18,079
Working overtime on my first day?

511
00:28:18,240 --> 00:28:19,160
You're a civil servant.

512
00:28:19,160 --> 00:28:20,319
Work overtime if necessary.

513
00:28:22,720 --> 00:28:24,440
I'll write half today.

514
00:28:24,599 --> 00:28:25,640
Finish it here.

515
00:28:26,880 --> 00:28:28,000
Zhitao, see you tomorrow.

516
00:28:28,599 --> 00:28:29,240
Stop.

517
00:28:32,400 --> 00:28:34,079
Why can she leave?

518
00:28:34,519 --> 00:28:36,240
Because I'm on a contractual basis.

519
00:28:36,839 --> 00:28:37,759
See you tomorrow.

520
00:28:47,039 --> 00:28:48,079
Stop wasting time.

521
00:29:12,519 --> 00:29:13,559
Did you use my computer?

522
00:29:14,480 --> 00:29:15,319
Why would I?

523
00:29:15,319 --> 00:29:16,559
I haven't even figured out

524
00:29:16,559 --> 00:29:17,519
how to use mine.

525
00:29:17,519 --> 00:29:18,920
Who are you yelling at?

526
00:29:19,599 --> 00:29:21,359
You yelled at me first.

527
00:29:39,119 --> 00:29:39,799
Rinse your mouth.

528
00:29:41,079 --> 00:29:42,000
I thought

529
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:44,319
you'd spend more time with me
after the transfer.

530
00:29:44,319 --> 00:29:45,880
I thought so too.

531
00:29:45,880 --> 00:29:48,240
She examines that report word by word.

532
00:29:48,319 --> 00:29:50,160
Win the battle but lose the war.

533
00:29:51,079 --> 00:29:51,880
Not even

534
00:29:51,880 --> 00:29:53,504
my primary school teacher was so strict.

535
00:29:54,720 --> 00:29:55,960
You can't blame her.

536
00:29:55,960 --> 00:29:57,960
Even your love letters
were full of typos.

537
00:29:58,440 --> 00:29:59,559
Who are you siding with?

538
00:30:00,759 --> 00:30:01,960
Even if there were typos,

539
00:30:01,960 --> 00:30:03,440
my letters were filled with love.

540
00:30:03,519 --> 00:30:04,880
I'm definitely on your side.

541
00:30:04,880 --> 00:30:05,799
You got this.

542
00:30:05,799 --> 00:30:06,720
You'll turn the tide.

543
00:30:08,400 --> 00:30:09,799
Chief Prosecutor Zheng

544
00:30:09,799 --> 00:30:11,720
told me to utilize my experience.

545
00:30:12,240 --> 00:30:15,160
H-How am I going to do that?

546
00:30:15,359 --> 00:30:16,279
Do you think

547
00:30:16,279 --> 00:30:17,599
Lin Zhitao wants me gone?

548
00:30:18,599 --> 00:30:19,480
In that case,

549
00:30:19,480 --> 00:30:20,480
I will resign

550
00:30:20,480 --> 00:30:21,480
and help you out.

551
00:30:21,480 --> 00:30:22,799
I'll be my own boss.

552
00:30:22,799 --> 00:30:24,039
Please don't.

553
00:30:24,400 --> 00:30:26,440
Our mortgage isn't fully paid off yet.

554
00:30:26,559 --> 00:30:28,079
I can't pay you.

555
00:30:28,519 --> 00:30:30,079
Besides, the job at the procuratorate

556
00:30:30,400 --> 00:30:31,440
is quite good.

557
00:30:32,720 --> 00:30:35,720
At least, I can reach you at any time.

558
00:30:35,720 --> 00:30:37,480
And you can come home every day.

559
00:30:38,480 --> 00:30:39,799
I'm more than happy.

560
00:30:41,200 --> 00:30:42,519
And those files

561
00:30:43,119 --> 00:30:44,160
I've been reading

562
00:30:44,160 --> 00:30:45,440
almost drove me mad.

563
00:30:46,480 --> 00:30:47,559
The couple divorced.

564
00:30:47,559 --> 00:30:49,119
Nobody took care of the child.

565
00:30:49,359 --> 00:30:51,279
They nearly starved the child to death.

566
00:30:51,279 --> 00:30:52,079
Infuriating, huh?

567
00:30:53,359 --> 00:30:56,759
Everything is so shocking.

568
00:30:57,160 --> 00:30:58,480
What a mess.

569
00:30:58,839 --> 00:31:00,440
Don't let our child hear this.

570
00:31:00,640 --> 00:31:01,599
You're right.

571
00:31:02,799 --> 00:31:04,400
I'll be on standby 24-7

572
00:31:04,400 --> 00:31:05,880
to protect you and the child.

573
00:31:07,400 --> 00:31:08,119
Protect us.

574
00:31:08,119 --> 00:31:09,519
Of course.

575
00:31:09,880 --> 00:31:10,440
Of course.

576
00:31:11,480 --> 00:31:12,799
I'll protect you.

577
00:31:12,799 --> 00:31:15,520
