(Bai Enyu, Lin Zhitao)

579
00:31:18,976 --> 00:31:19,799
(Li Qinxun)
Chief Prosecutor.

580
00:31:19,799 --> 00:31:20,359
Hello.

581
00:31:24,224 --> 00:31:24,920
Have a seat.

582
00:31:25,200 --> 00:31:25,759
Have a seat.

583
00:31:34,519 --> 00:31:36,079
Please introduce them.

584
00:31:36,759 --> 00:31:37,720
Okay.

585
00:31:38,440 --> 00:31:39,519
These two are staff

586
00:31:39,519 --> 00:31:42,359
responsible for juvenile aid
from the civil affairs bureau.

587
00:31:42,480 --> 00:31:44,920
This is Professor Xiao Bingli,
the renowned jurist,

588
00:31:44,920 --> 00:31:46,440
and the Vice Dean of the Law School

589
00:31:46,799 --> 00:31:49,720
from the Southern University
of Political Science and Law.

590
00:31:51,160 --> 00:31:52,240
(Xiao Bingli)
This is his apprentice,

591
00:31:52,440 --> 00:31:53,880
Attorney Li Daoran.

592
00:31:54,519 --> 00:31:55,200
Hello, sir.

593
00:31:55,279 --> 00:31:56,400
(Li Qinxun)
Let's get started.

594
00:31:56,400 --> 00:31:56,920
Okay.

595
00:31:57,240 --> 00:31:58,519
You will host

596
00:31:58,799 --> 00:31:59,720
today's seminar.

597
00:31:59,744 --> 00:32:00,608
Is this appropriate?

598
00:32:00,880 --> 00:32:01,632
Of course.

599
00:32:02,519 --> 00:32:04,079
You invited everyone here.

600
00:32:05,200 --> 00:32:06,319
I'm just a listener.

601
00:32:07,119 --> 00:32:07,720
Alright.

602
00:32:09,559 --> 00:32:10,359
So.

603
00:32:11,039 --> 00:32:12,920
Today's meeting is about

604
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:16,599
whether to revoke
Lu Guangfu's guardianship

605
00:32:16,599 --> 00:32:18,400
after his release.

606
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:20,400
We invited you here

607
00:32:21,079 --> 00:32:22,079
mainly because

608
00:32:22,559 --> 00:32:23,640
there has not yet

609
00:32:23,640 --> 00:32:25,119
been a precedent in the country.

610
00:32:25,119 --> 00:32:27,400
Lu Sheng and Lu Ming
won't be with Lu Guangfu anymore?

611
00:32:27,599 --> 00:32:28,519
Isn't that good?

612
00:32:28,519 --> 00:32:29,480
What's there to discuss?

613
00:32:29,480 --> 00:32:30,400
Stop talking.

614
00:32:31,200 --> 00:32:31,799
Just listen.

615
00:32:32,839 --> 00:32:35,319
Prosecutor Lin and I

616
00:32:35,440 --> 00:32:37,480
are both students of Mr. Xiao.

617
00:32:38,519 --> 00:32:40,519
They are both my star pupils.

618
00:32:40,519 --> 00:32:43,240
I'm honored and flattered

619
00:32:43,240 --> 00:32:46,559
to be invited to this seminar

620
00:32:46,559 --> 00:32:49,559
and I'm glad to see my mentor.

621
00:32:51,720 --> 00:32:52,759
I will be the first

622
00:32:52,960 --> 00:32:54,039
to speak as a junior.

623
00:32:54,119 --> 00:32:57,119
Let me offer my humble opinion

624
00:32:57,440 --> 00:32:58,559
and share

625
00:32:58,599 --> 00:33:00,599
the perspectives

626
00:33:00,599 --> 00:33:03,720
of us legal practitioners.

627
00:33:04,160 --> 00:33:06,160
(Li Qinxun)
Here's my major concern.

628
00:33:06,160 --> 00:33:08,319
The Civil Affairs Department

629
00:33:08,319 --> 00:33:10,319
may be the primary entity
in this lawsuit.

630
00:33:10,319 --> 00:33:11,119
However,

631
00:33:11,119 --> 00:33:13,119
it is initiated by the procuratorate.

632
00:33:13,440 --> 00:33:14,400
To push it forward,

633
00:33:14,400 --> 00:33:16,720
as the legal supervisory body
of the state,

634
00:33:16,759 --> 00:33:18,000
will it appear

635
00:33:18,160 --> 00:33:19,880
to the public

636
00:33:19,880 --> 00:33:22,519
that public authority
is too overpowering

637
00:33:22,519 --> 00:33:24,240
in this legal practice?

638
00:33:25,039 --> 00:33:27,160
Shall we ignore the issue
because we fear questioning?

639
00:33:27,160 --> 00:33:28,279
We are not ignoring it.

640
00:33:28,720 --> 00:33:29,720
Prosecutor Lin,

641
00:33:29,720 --> 00:33:31,200
have you heard this saying?

642
00:33:31,720 --> 00:33:32,720
"The wind, rain,"

643
00:33:33,039 --> 00:33:34,640
"and storm may enter,"

644
00:33:34,880 --> 00:33:36,160
"but the king cannot."

645
00:33:36,440 --> 00:33:37,440
It means

646
00:33:37,920 --> 00:33:40,200
the law protects
the private property of citizens.

647
00:33:40,599 --> 00:33:42,400
But children are never the property

648
00:33:42,599 --> 00:33:43,480
of their parents.

649
00:33:46,599 --> 00:33:48,960
We are now discussing
the practical difficulties.

650
00:33:49,759 --> 00:33:50,839
After all,

651
00:33:50,839 --> 00:33:52,319
we haven't found

652
00:33:52,400 --> 00:33:53,480
a suitable guardian.

653
00:33:54,240 --> 00:33:55,119
These two children

654
00:33:55,119 --> 00:33:57,440
shall be handed over
to the Civil Affairs Department.

655
00:34:00,079 --> 00:34:01,440
We have only one concern.

656
00:34:01,759 --> 00:34:03,200
Once this matter gets out,

657
00:34:03,599 --> 00:34:05,039
will it remind those

658
00:34:05,039 --> 00:34:06,200
irresponsible parents

659
00:34:06,519 --> 00:34:07,319
to leave their kids

660
00:34:07,319 --> 00:34:08,559
to the state?

661
00:34:08,719 --> 00:34:09,440
I think

662
00:34:09,599 --> 00:34:11,239
our funding is very limited.

663
00:34:11,760 --> 00:34:12,880
Revoking guardianship

664
00:34:12,880 --> 00:34:14,440
requires evaluation.

665
00:34:14,519 --> 00:34:15,519
The harm to the kids

666
00:34:15,519 --> 00:34:17,440
will be severe enough to constitute

667
00:34:17,440 --> 00:34:18,360
criminal cases.

668
00:34:19,239 --> 00:34:21,280
Would anyone commit a crime

669
00:34:21,280 --> 00:34:23,000
just to leave their kids to the state?

670
00:34:24,384 --> 00:34:25,952
As long as there are other constraints,

671
00:34:26,079 --> 00:34:27,232
we are happy to cooperate.

672
00:34:28,000 --> 00:34:28,360
Okay.

673
00:34:29,039 --> 00:34:31,199
The procuratorate, in essence,

674
00:34:31,199 --> 00:34:35,039
is a state institution
representing public power.

675
00:34:35,039 --> 00:34:35,880
When

676
00:34:35,880 --> 00:34:39,559
a state institution interferes with
family ties between parents

677
00:34:39,559 --> 00:34:40,760
and children,

678
00:34:41,119 --> 00:34:44,760
it will surely cause panic
and uncertainty

679
00:34:45,119 --> 00:34:46,159
among the public.

680
00:34:46,480 --> 00:34:48,079
"Your children are not yours."

681
00:34:48,199 --> 00:34:49,039
For now,

682
00:34:49,320 --> 00:34:50,639
this concept is quite

683
00:34:50,800 --> 00:34:52,639
challenging to the public.

684
00:34:53,360 --> 00:34:54,400
It increases

685
00:34:54,480 --> 00:34:57,400
invisible social risks.

686
00:34:58,360 --> 00:34:59,239
Mr. Xiao.

687
00:34:59,960 --> 00:35:02,000
There are prerequisites
for this procedure.

688
00:35:02,320 --> 00:35:03,159
In this case,

689
00:35:03,159 --> 00:35:05,599
Lu Guangfu is an alcoholic
and commits domestic violence.

690
00:35:05,599 --> 00:35:07,079
He sequentially rented out

691
00:35:07,079 --> 00:35:09,159
his two children to criminal gangs.

692
00:35:09,159 --> 00:35:10,119
Please tell me.

693
00:35:10,280 --> 00:35:12,440
Why would normal families be concerned

694
00:35:12,440 --> 00:35:13,920
when we revoke a father like him

695
00:35:14,440 --> 00:35:16,280
of his guardianship?

696
00:35:16,280 --> 00:35:17,400
Is there a problem?

697
00:35:17,519 --> 00:35:19,079
What we are discussing now

698
00:35:19,079 --> 00:35:22,039
are broad legal principles
and social issues,

699
00:35:22,360 --> 00:35:24,599
not just an individual case.

700
00:35:24,880 --> 00:35:26,519
Legal principles exist

701
00:35:27,159 --> 00:35:28,320
exactly to ensure

702
00:35:28,440 --> 00:35:31,320
the greatest happiness
of the greatest mass.

703
00:35:32,239 --> 00:35:34,440
Should we sacrifice a child's future

704
00:35:34,760 --> 00:35:36,280
for intangible legal principles?

705
00:35:38,400 --> 00:35:39,440
Do you have a child?

706
00:35:39,760 --> 00:35:40,639
No.

707
00:35:40,639 --> 00:35:42,039
Have you conducted research?

708
00:35:42,159 --> 00:35:43,119
Yes, I have.

709
00:35:43,199 --> 00:35:45,079
How many parents do you know

710
00:35:45,519 --> 00:35:47,559
and you dare to openly challenge

711
00:35:47,559 --> 00:35:49,840
the established legal provisions?

712
00:35:51,000 --> 00:35:53,280
I think you'd better go back

713
00:35:53,280 --> 00:35:54,599
and read over

714
00:35:54,599 --> 00:35:55,920
those textbooks again

715
00:35:56,039 --> 00:35:58,360
before coming back to discuss with me

716
00:35:58,360 --> 00:36:00,239
whether the law should serve individuals

717
00:36:00,400 --> 00:36:01,800
or society as a whole.

718
00:36:01,800 --> 00:36:03,159
What is society composed of?

719
00:36:03,440 --> 00:36:04,360
Society?

720
00:36:05,519 --> 00:36:06,599
Legal researchers

721
00:36:07,119 --> 00:36:08,360
like us

722
00:36:08,519 --> 00:36:10,920
should focus on the societal impact

723
00:36:11,159 --> 00:36:13,280
rather than the problems
of an individual.

724
00:36:13,480 --> 00:36:16,960
Without thorough research,
experimentation,

725
00:36:17,639 --> 00:36:19,519
and summarization,

726
00:36:19,519 --> 00:36:20,199
I believe

727
00:36:20,440 --> 00:36:23,360
that any conclusion would have flaws.

728
00:36:23,599 --> 00:36:25,559
We must objectively and thoroughly

729
00:36:25,960 --> 00:36:28,119
understand the issues

730
00:36:28,440 --> 00:36:30,280
before we utilize social forces

731
00:36:30,280 --> 00:36:31,360
to conduct research,

732
00:36:31,719 --> 00:36:34,320
invite experts and scholars

733
00:36:34,599 --> 00:36:35,760
to discussions,

734
00:36:35,760 --> 00:36:37,800
and write papers for a comprehensive...

735
00:36:37,800 --> 00:36:38,760
By that time,

736
00:36:38,760 --> 00:36:40,840
that child would have been in prison.

737
00:36:42,760 --> 00:36:43,760
I was just wondering.

738
00:36:44,039 --> 00:36:45,400
Didn't you major in massage?

739
00:36:45,880 --> 00:36:47,760
I'm working on that
at the juvenile prosecution.

740
00:36:49,519 --> 00:36:50,880
Prosecutor Zheng recommended him.

741
00:36:51,079 --> 00:36:51,840
I approved.

742
00:36:53,199 --> 00:36:53,880
Sir.

743
00:36:54,400 --> 00:36:55,400
May I speak?

744
00:36:56,320 --> 00:36:56,800
Go ahead.

745
00:36:58,800 --> 00:36:59,719
Professor Xiao, right?

746
00:37:00,039 --> 00:37:01,400
I think you are very smart.

747
00:37:01,840 --> 00:37:03,360
You know what I mean?

748
00:37:03,960 --> 00:37:05,480
You seem to have said everything,

749
00:37:05,480 --> 00:37:07,159
but you haven't said anything at all.

750
00:37:07,559 --> 00:37:09,039
Let's be practical.

751
00:37:09,519 --> 00:37:10,920
There was a difficult child

752
00:37:10,920 --> 00:37:12,559
at the Juvenile Correctional Facility.

753
00:37:12,800 --> 00:37:13,840
The instructor told him,

754
00:37:13,840 --> 00:37:14,760
"Be optimistic.

755
00:37:14,760 --> 00:37:16,280
Live your life positively."

756
00:37:16,599 --> 00:37:19,159
He said, "Even my dad
doesn't care about me."

757
00:37:19,639 --> 00:37:21,960
"He only loves his sons
born to his mistresses."

758
00:37:21,960 --> 00:37:23,280
"How can I be selfless,"

759
00:37:23,280 --> 00:37:24,320
"law-abiding,"

760
00:37:24,320 --> 00:37:26,039
"and optimistic about life?"

761
00:37:26,039 --> 00:37:27,159
The instructor said,

762
00:37:27,280 --> 00:37:28,760
"Stop complaining."

763
00:37:29,039 --> 00:37:31,440
"Face your problems and solve them."

764
00:37:31,760 --> 00:37:32,360
He said

765
00:37:32,360 --> 00:37:34,000
that problems can be solved,

766
00:37:34,000 --> 00:37:36,400
but the challenge of his life

767
00:37:36,400 --> 00:37:38,159
lies in his family background.

768
00:37:38,880 --> 00:37:39,480
The parents

769
00:37:39,480 --> 00:37:41,400
can choose whether to have children.

770
00:37:41,559 --> 00:37:44,119
But children don't have the right
to choose their parents.

771
00:37:44,719 --> 00:37:45,800
When they are born,

772
00:37:45,800 --> 00:37:46,880
no one tells them

773
00:37:47,199 --> 00:37:49,519
whether their parents are qualified.

774
00:37:49,800 --> 00:37:52,480
You said it was an individual issue,

775
00:37:52,480 --> 00:37:54,039
not a societal one.

776
00:37:54,280 --> 00:37:55,400
But I'm telling you,

777
00:37:56,079 --> 00:37:57,519
those kids in the facility

778
00:37:58,079 --> 00:38:00,360
are generally facing the same problem.

779
00:38:00,360 --> 00:38:01,639
The kids you mentioned

780
00:38:02,079 --> 00:38:03,440
have already committed crimes.

781
00:38:06,039 --> 00:38:08,159
So they're not kids anymore?

782
00:38:09,159 --> 00:38:10,199
Tell you what.

783
00:38:10,199 --> 00:38:11,599
Without irresponsible parents,

784
00:38:11,599 --> 00:38:13,360
those children might not commit crimes.

785
00:38:13,360 --> 00:38:14,239
Sit down, Bai Enyu.

786
00:38:15,280 --> 00:38:17,280
You said Prosecutor Lin
didn't study this issue.

787
00:38:17,280 --> 00:38:18,280
Did you?

788
00:38:18,280 --> 00:38:19,760
Do you know this child?

789
00:38:19,760 --> 00:38:21,039
Have you cared about him?

790
00:38:21,199 --> 00:38:22,159
How big is his family?

791
00:38:22,280 --> 00:38:24,119
What his alcoholic father
and his looney mother

792
00:38:24,239 --> 00:38:25,360
are getting by?

793
00:38:25,360 --> 00:38:26,400
Do you know?

794
00:38:26,639 --> 00:38:28,400
Do you know how many adults

795
00:38:28,400 --> 00:38:30,119
are not qualified to be parents?

796
00:38:30,639 --> 00:38:31,400
Now I understand

797
00:38:31,400 --> 00:38:32,280
why she made me

798
00:38:32,280 --> 00:38:33,920
read those case files.

799
00:38:34,320 --> 00:38:36,880
Abuse, abandonment, rape.

800
00:38:37,320 --> 00:38:38,320
Are you saying

801
00:38:38,480 --> 00:38:39,239
those kids

802
00:38:39,239 --> 00:38:41,079
should stay with those human filth

803
00:38:41,079 --> 00:38:42,280
and we have no say in it?

804
00:38:42,519 --> 00:38:44,840
We are discussing legal principles.

805
00:38:45,079 --> 00:38:45,960
What are you doing?

806
00:38:46,599 --> 00:38:48,280
Telling stories? Stirring emotions?

807
00:38:48,320 --> 00:38:50,000
Generalizing from a partial standpoint?

808
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:51,559
What are the names of these kids?

809
00:38:54,440 --> 00:38:56,840
Now you remember to read the files?

810
00:38:56,840 --> 00:38:58,519
From the moment you entered,

811
00:38:58,519 --> 00:38:59,840
you've never mentioned

812
00:38:59,840 --> 00:39:01,239
the names of these kids.

813
00:39:01,360 --> 00:39:02,800
The law is majestic.

814
00:39:02,800 --> 00:39:03,480
But tell me.

815
00:39:03,480 --> 00:39:04,920
For whom does it exist?

816
00:39:05,880 --> 00:39:07,480
You didn't answer my question.

817
00:39:07,960 --> 00:39:09,480
You keep talking about the majority

818
00:39:09,480 --> 00:39:10,599
and society.

819
00:39:10,960 --> 00:39:11,639
Tell me.

820
00:39:11,639 --> 00:39:13,119
What is society composed of?

821
00:39:17,880 --> 00:39:18,960
Individuals.

822
00:39:19,760 --> 00:39:22,280
It's composed of individuals.

823
00:39:22,320 --> 00:39:24,079
Each of us was once a child.

824
00:39:24,079 --> 00:39:24,719
Right?

825
00:39:24,960 --> 00:39:26,320
Can we possibly

826
00:39:26,320 --> 00:39:27,719
save Lu Ming this time?

827
00:39:27,719 --> 00:39:28,800
Can we help him once?

828
00:39:29,079 --> 00:39:30,039
I hope we can

829
00:39:31,400 --> 00:39:32,280
give him a chance.

830
00:39:32,599 --> 00:39:34,000
Where is your rationality?

831
00:39:34,280 --> 00:39:36,599
Don't claim to be my student
from now on.

832
00:39:36,960 --> 00:39:38,639
I am not your student, am I?

833
00:39:39,119 --> 00:39:39,760
You...

834
00:39:40,000 --> 00:39:40,599
Prosecutor Fu.

835
00:39:41,119 --> 00:39:42,800
I didn't ask to come today.

836
00:39:43,199 --> 00:39:44,639
You invited me here.

837
00:39:44,639 --> 00:39:46,320
What's that attitude?

838
00:39:46,320 --> 00:39:47,519
Mr. Xiao, don't be upset.

839
00:39:47,880 --> 00:39:48,960
Bai Enyu, get out.

840
00:39:48,960 --> 00:39:49,760
He won't.

841
00:39:49,760 --> 00:39:50,719
He said nothing wrong.

842
00:39:50,719 --> 00:39:52,360
Why should I leave? We are colleagues.

843
00:39:52,360 --> 00:39:53,360
Unreasonable.

844
00:39:53,360 --> 00:39:54,480
Oh, come on.

845
00:39:54,480 --> 00:39:55,360
Show some respect.

846
00:39:55,599 --> 00:39:56,639
Want to argue, huh?

847
00:39:56,639 --> 00:39:58,000
Bring the wind and storm.

848
00:39:58,000 --> 00:39:59,320
Let the king into the hut.

849
00:39:59,320 --> 00:40:00,039
Excuse me.

850
00:40:00,039 --> 00:40:01,920
That was a legal proverb.

851
00:40:01,920 --> 00:40:02,920
I know legal idioms.

852
00:40:02,920 --> 00:40:04,280
But you don't know the law.

853
00:40:04,440 --> 00:40:06,000
Sorry, I am late.

854
00:40:06,000 --> 00:40:06,599
Madam.

855
00:40:10,119 --> 00:40:11,480
The plane just landed

856
00:40:11,480 --> 00:40:13,039
and I heard that

857
00:40:13,239 --> 00:40:14,239
you were holding

858
00:40:14,239 --> 00:40:15,480
an important seminar.

859
00:40:15,519 --> 00:40:17,280
Professor Xiao was lecturing us.

860
00:40:17,280 --> 00:40:18,360
Is it about

861
00:40:18,360 --> 00:40:20,280
revoking Lu Guangfu's guardianship?

862
00:40:20,480 --> 00:40:21,159
That's right.

863
00:40:21,159 --> 00:40:22,719
It was a heated discussion.

864
00:40:26,559 --> 00:40:28,199
The meeting at the SPP

865
00:40:28,880 --> 00:40:30,159
also addressed this issue.

866
00:40:30,840 --> 00:40:31,480
The SPP

867
00:40:31,480 --> 00:40:33,320
attaches great importance

868
00:40:33,320 --> 00:40:34,519
